{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Culture of the People's Republic of China |nativename = {{nobold|{{lang|zh-hans|中华人民共和国文化部}}}} |nativename_r = {{small|''Zhōnghuá Rénmín Gònghéguó Wénhuàbù}} |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal =National Emblem of the People's Republic of China.svg |seal_width =150px |seal_caption =[[Emblem of the People's Republic of China]] |formed =September 1954 |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = March 19, 2018 |superseding = [[Ministry of Culture and Tourism of the People's Republic of China|Ministry of Culture and Tourism]] |jurisdiction = {{PRC}} |headquarters = [[Beijing]] |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = [[Luo Shugang]] |minister1_pfo = |parent_agency = [[State Council of the People's Republic of China|State Council]] |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = {{url|www.mcprc.gov.cn}} |footnotes = }} The '''Ministry of Culture''' ('''MOC''') was a [[ministry (government)|ministry]] of the [[government of the People's Republic of China]] which was dissolved on March 19, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://www.ce.cn/culture/gd/201803/19/t20180319_28524714.shtml |script-title=zh:雒树刚被任命为首位文化和旅游部部长（附简历） |newspaper=ce.cn |date=2018-03-19 |language=zh}}</ref> The responsibilities of the MOC, which were assumed by the [[Ministry of Culture and Tourism of the People's Republic of China|Ministry of Culture and Tourism]], encompassed [[cultural policy]] and activities in the country, including managing national museums and monuments; promoting and protecting the arts (including censorship of visual, folk, theatrical, musical, dance, architectural, literary, televisual and cinematographic works); and managing the national archives and regional culture centers. Its headquarters were in [[Chaoyang District, Beijing|Chaoyang District]], [[Beijing]].<ref>[http://www.ccnt.gov.cn/English/index.html Home] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101206225425/http://ccnt.gov.cn/English/index.html |date=2010-12-06 }}. Ministry of Culture of the People's Republic of China. Retrieved on December 22, 2010. "Contact us Address: No.10, Chaoyangmen Beidajie, Chaoyang District, Beijing,100020 Tel:86-10-59881114"</ref>
== Duties == {{See also|Public domain|Right to science and culture}}
The duty of the ministry was to [[Digital preservation|digitize and preserve]] public domain works, and make them available and accessible to every citizen. China had millions of public domain works, including but not limited to books, pictures, [[Public domain music|music]] and [[Public domain film|films]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://dl.psnc.pl/2010/07/30/european-libraries-and-google-cooperate-in-digitization/ |title=European libraries and Google cooperate in digitization - Digital Libraries and Knowledge Platforms Department|first=Marcin|last=Mielnicki }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.communia-association.org/2015/12/05/public-domain-on-trial-in-mannheims-reiss-engelhorn-museum-vs-wikimedia-et-al/ |title=Public Domain on Trial in Reiss-Engelhorn Museum vs. Wikimedia et al. |first=Leonhard|last=Dobusch|date=5 December 2015 }}</ref>
