{{Expand Swedish|Revolutionära fronten|date=September 2018}} The '''Revolutionary Front''' ({{lang-sv|Revolutionära fronten}}) was a [[Far-left politics|far-left]] extremist political and militant movement in [[Sweden]]. The goal of the RF was to dismantle the current society through a [[revolution]] and create a [[socialist state]]. The group fought against [[fascism]], [[racism]], [[sexism]] and [[capitalism]], and campaigned through violent means.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sv.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Uppdrag_granskning&oldid=43067589|title=Uppdrag granskning|date=3 June 2018|publisher=|via=Wikipedia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://redice.tv/news/the-rise-of-sweden-s-far-left-militants-sweden-is-being-divided-and-conquered-by-design|title=The Rise Of Sweden’s Far-Left Militants - Sweden is being Divided and Conquered by Design|website=redice.tv}}</ref>
The Revolutionary Front was formed in 2002 by Joel Bjurströmer Almgren and others. In 2014 Almgren was sentenced to five years in prison for stabbing a [[Neo-Nazism|neo-Nazi]] in the back during the violent [[December 2013 Stockholm riots]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/nyheter/sankt-fangelsestraff-for-vansterextremist/|title=Sänkt fängelsestraff för vänsterextremist - Nyheter - Expressen|publisher=}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thelocal.se/20140521/sweden-jails-extreme-leftists-for-slovak-mix-up|title=Sweden jails extreme leftists for Slovak mix-up|date=21 May 2014|publisher=}}</ref> In September 2015 the organisation dissolved.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hd.se/2015-09-27/revolutionara-fronten-lagger-ned|title=Revolutionära fronten lägger ned|publisher=}}</ref><ref>https://www.metro.se/artikel/revolutionära-fronten-lägger-ned-xr</ref>
