The '''Unconditional Divisions''' were elite sub-units of the military forces of the [[Khmer Rouge]] regime of Cambodia. Unit members were personally loyal to [[Pol Pot]],<ref name="RossDivision1990">{{cite book|author1=Russell R. Ross|author2=Library of Congress. Federal Research Division|title=Cambodia: a country study|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zXUsAAAAYAAJ|date=1 May 1990|publisher=The Division|page=54}}</ref> and under the direct control of the Central Committee.<ref name="Etcheson1984">{{cite book|author=Craig Etcheson|title=The rise and demise of Democratic Kampuchea|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UHFuAAAAMAAJ|year=1984|publisher=Westview|page=167}}</ref>
